caption: There seems to be a glitch attaching positive views from another restaurant to this place so I figured I’d throw a review in. I was offered a coupon on DoorDash and thought the prices looked great so I went ahead and ordered a pie and chicken wings. Pretty awful lol. I didn’t finish my pizza and my roommate didn’t either. The ‘BK’ in the name threw me off for sure. This place is essentially Little Caesars only a bit more expensive. If you are trying to get a few pepperoni pizzas for a kids’ bday or something, it’s certainly an affordable option - but it is really just ‘fast food pizza’, and even that classification is generous. I would rather have eaten almost any other chain pizza. Like I said if you wanna order a few pies for a party it’s definitely affordable so go ahead and try it but definitely stay away from the wings - they are the saltiest I’ve ever had. Almost inedible.

I am baffled as to how this place has 5 stars. I will never order from here again (maybe as a walk in) but not delivery. I ordered $50 worth of food and the postmates driver marked himself off as completed (while I watched down my block waiting for him and saw no one in sight). He never delivered the food and I've been on the phone with Bk Pizza for 45m total trying to get this sorted out. After all that time they agreed to remake my food and I had to send my three teenagers to pick it up in pitch cold darkness. They refused to take responsibility as the merchant and I had no way of contacting this driver. Not only that, my children are standing there right now as I type this, because they bagged a square and triangle pizza instead of two regular cheese pies. UNREAL!!!!
